Tools for B-parking data

-----------------------------------------

# Checkout
mkdir myWork
cd myWork/
git clone https://github.com/crovelli/BParkAnalysisTools.git
cd BParkAnalysisTools
git checkout MarchProd
mkdir lib

# Edit include/Application.hh to chose the program to run, i.e. 1 for TnP 

# Compile: 
make all

# Run:
./BParkApp  -> will give you the list of needed inputs.

E.g. for TnP:
./BParkApp inputFile [outputFile] [1=MC,0=data] [dataset]

./BParkApp myInputFile.txt myOutput 1 signal

where myInputFile.txt is a txt file with the list of ntuples, e.g. obtained with

ls /eos/cms/store/group/phys_bphys/crovelli/nanoaod_RK/BParkingNANO_2022Dec14/BuToKJpsi_Toee_Mufilter_SoftQCDnonD_TuneCP5_13TeV-pythia8-evtgen/crab_BuToKJpsi_Toee/221214_135543/0000/BParkNANO_mc_2022Dec14_19.root > myInputFile.txt